						<summary>

						<p>Damaged. Refers to the gift of a flower garden. The gift seems to have been formally made by the sons of a certain <hi rend="bold">Kodama Siṁhamu</hi> with the consent of all the villagers. The name of the village is lost. The dimensions of the several lines of the trees are given in terms of arm's length <hi rend="italic">(chētulu).</hi> Refers to the <hi rend="bold">Kākatīya</hi> king <hi rend="bold">Rudradēva-Mahārāja.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
